                <h4>
                    The company makes regular donations of essential pharmaceuticals to conduct free medical camps to needy people. Company also donates funds regularly to different welfare societies in the country in order to improve their quality of life of the sick, aged or deprived children. Contributions are also made to government hospitals to develop and maintain wards and different treatment units

                    ABC Pharma Services made a donation of essential pharmaceuticals to the value of USD 75,408.23 to ministry of health. The directors of ABC handed over the consignment to (Then). Minister of Healthcare Hon. Nimal Siripala De Silva. Also present was The Director- Medical Technology & Supplies – Dr. Hemantha Beneragama.

                    Octpharma AG made a donation of 5819 bottles of Human Albumin 20% with an approximate value of USD 100,000.00 to the Ministry of Healthcare. The Managing Director of ABC handed over the documents pertaining to the shipment to the Hon. Minister of Health.

                    Novartis Thailand and Sandoz GmbH, Germany donated a consignment of Anti-biotics and anti-ulcer drugs to the value of USD 140,000.00 to the Ministry of Healthcare of Sri Lanka.

                    At the time of Asian Tsunamii the employees of ABC Pharma Services rallied around spontaneously to reach out to the afflicted. The employees voluntarily agreed to the cancellation of the Staff party and wanted all expenses related to this event transferred to a Tsunami Victims fund. They also contributed a day’s wage towards this fund. These collections were equally matched by the company.
